description._content:
Catalog #: 15_001611
Title: Boeing B-17G Flying Fortress
ADDITIONAL INFORMATION: Delivered to USAAF as 44-85643. Eventually to the Instituit Geographique National, Creil, France  from December 12, 1947-1989 as F-BEEA, as ""Chateau de Verneuil"". Used for aerial survey work in Europe, Africa, and Papua-New Guinea. Flown in the 1989 film ""Memphis Belle"" as ""Baby Ruth"". Destroyed on takeoff at RAF Binbrook, UK, in July of 1989. Aircraft destroyed but crew escaped with no fatalities.
